# Phase 8.7 — Content Agent Acceptance Proof Rules

This rule applies only to Step 8.7 of Phase 8.

## Scope

Prove Phase 8 acceptance criteria with deterministic tests and a validated example output document.

## Rules

1. Focus on acceptance proof, validation coverage, and example output only.
2. Do not implement major new Content Agent features unless a tiny fix is required to make existing 8.1–8.6 behavior testable.
3. Add `docs/examples/content_output.json` and validate it against `ContentSuggestions`.
4. Add `agents/content/tests/test_content_output_example.py` and `agents/content/tests/test_phase8_acceptance.py` (or equivalent) proving Phase 8 acceptance criteria.
5. Add deterministic tests proving:
   - at least one `content.instagram_draft` for a Prestia-style product fixture or seeded Prestia product
   - `content.product_description` draft generation works
   - generated output validates against `ContentSuggestions`
   - configured max draft limit is respected
   - Persian default output path works end-to-end through pipeline or `POST /run`
   - English output works with `AI_OUTPUT_LANGUAGE=en` end-to-end through pipeline or `POST /run`
   - content action mapping preserves approval-required behavior
   - only `content.instagram_draft` and `content.product_description` are accepted
6. Prefer the highest practical test layer: `POST /run` when stable, otherwise `run_content_analysis()` and Step 8.6 action mapping helpers.
7. Use MockProvider, fixtures, or seeded test data only. Do not require real LLM API keys or external services.
8. Do not implement real Instagram publishing, external side effects, competitor scraping, website article generation, Support Agent logic, Coordinator/LangGraph orchestration, or frontend work.
9. Do not hardcode Prestia-specific business logic in agent code. Prestia-style data may appear only in tests, fixtures, seed/demo data, or example documentation.
10. Do not auto-approve or auto-execute content actions.
11. Keep all action behavior inside the Django approval workflow.
12. Preserve Steps 8.1–8.6 behavior and existing Sales Agent, backend action, and health-check tests.
13. Update `docs/phases/step-8.7.md` with acceptance evidence, files changed, validation commands, example output details, Persian/English validation notes, and final Phase 8 status.
